        "heading_path": [
          "Insect bites and stings: antimicrobial prescribing",
          "Recommendations",
          "1.1 Managing insect bites and stings",
          "Assessment and advice",
          "1.1.1"
        ],
        "dom_section_identifier": "nice-insect-bites-ng182-2020-section-0006",
        "position": 5,
        "paragraph_or_text_span": "Be aware that: a rapid-onset skin reaction from an insect bite or sting is likely to be an inflammatory or allergic reaction, rather than an infection most insect bites or stings will not need antibiotics.",
        "normalized_span_fingerprint": "5046ff7ecdb88f1a409189bbae8ce46ad38285010b93715597e334bc80a5bd60",
        "page_start": null,
        "page_end": null,
        "section_id": "nice-insect-bites-ng182-2020-section-0006"
      }
    },
    {
      "evidence_statement_id": "family-derm-insect--statement-00004",
      "source_id": "nice-insect-bites-ng182-2020",
      "official_source_url": "https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ng182/chapter/recommendations",
      "locator": {
        "source_id": "nice-insect-bites-ng182-2020",
        "resolved_url": "https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ng182/chapter/recommendations",
        "anchor": null,
        "heading_path": [
          "Insect bites and stings: antimicrobial prescribing",
          "Recommendations",
          "1.1 Managing insect bites and stings",
          "Assessment and advice",
          "1.1.2"
        ],
        "dom_section_identifier": "nice-insect-bites-ng182-2020-section-0007",
        "position": 6,
        "paragraph_or_text_span": "Assess the type and severity of the insect bite or stings to identify: a local inflammatory or allergic skin reaction erythema migrans (bullseye rash), a sign of Lyme disease (see the NICE guideline on Lyme disease ) symptoms or signs of an infection a systemic reaction (see the recommendations on referral and seeking specialist advice ).",
        "normalized_span_fingerprint": "921b932bf348f8f1dacf3bab8f238118e98d6f2b70cb7347c78a8dfc91d63840",
        "page_start": null,
        "page_end": null,
        "section_id": "nice-insect-bites-ng182-2020-section-0007"
      }
    },
    {
      "evidence_statement_id": "family-derm-insect--statement-00005",
      "source_id": "nice-insect-bites-ng182-2020",
      "official_source_url": "https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ng182/chapter/recommendations",
      "locator": {
        "source_id": "nice-insect-bites-ng182-2020",
        "resolved_url": "https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ng182/chapter/recommendations",
        "anchor": null,
        "heading_path": [
          "Insect bites and stings: antimicrobial prescribing",
          "Recommendations",
          "1.1 Managing insect bites and stings",
          "Assessment and advice",
          "1.1.3"
        ],
        "dom_section_identifier": "nice-insect-bites-ng182-2020-section-0008",
        "position": 7,
        "paragraph_or_text_span": "Advise people with an insect bite or sting that: a community pharmacist can advise about self‑care treatments skin redness and itching are common and may last for up to 10 days it is unlikely that the skin will become infected avoiding scratching may reduce inflammation and the risk of infection they should seek medical help if symptoms worsen rapidly or significantly at any time, or they become s",
        "normalized_span_fingerprint": "bd11ef3f4a37a35546e7e4bfa2736834130a870c7db02cf7d8de70cf4241c694",
        "page_start": null,
        "page_end": null,
        "section_id": "nice-insect-bites-ng182-2020-section-0008"
      }
    },
    {
      "evidence_statement_id": "family-derm-insect--statement-00006",
      "source_id": "nice-insect-bites-ng182-2020",
      "official_source_url": "https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ng182/chapter/recommendations",
      "locator": {
        "source_id": "nice-insect-bites-ng182-2020",
        "resolved_url": "https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ng182/chapter/recommendations",
        "anchor": null,
        "heading_path": [
          "Insect bites and stings: antimicrobial prescribing",
          "Recommendations",
          "1.1 Managing insect bites and stings",
          "Assessment and advice",
          "1.1.4"
        ],
        "dom_section_identifier": "nice-insect-bites-ng182-2020-section-0009",
        "position": 8,
        "paragraph_or_text_span": "For people with a known or suspected tick bite, follow the NICE guideline on Lyme disease . For a short explanation of why the committee made these recommendations, see the rationale section on assessment and advice . For more details, see the evidence review .",
        "normalized_span_fingerprint": "f61ff04e4b249c4cecfae220755da9b9656de05b3946b0f9aaadab5699477415",
        "page_start": null,
        "page_end": null,
        "section_id": "nice-insect-bites-ng182-2020-section-0009"
      }
    },
    {
      "evidence_statement_id": "family-derm-insect--statement-00007",
      "source_id": "nice-insect-bites-ng182-2020",
      "official_source_url": "https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ng182/chapter/recommendations",
      "locator": {
        "source_id": "nice-insect-bites-ng182-2020",
        "resolved_url": "https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ng182/chapter/recommendations",
        "anchor": null,
